summary: I think my most favorite song in Reputation is New Years Day, it's incredibly underwhelming and it doesn't have any flair like...
body:
I think my most favorite song in Reputation is New Years Day, it’s incredibly underwhelming and it doesn’t have any flair like all of the other songs and many overlooked it but what did it for me is that unsettling piano.

I questioned originally its lack of rhythm. Found it awkward and a minute in I was really craving for it to continue properly hoping it’ll change but it never did in the way I had hoped.

Instead, I was forced to focus on the lyrics instead and found them to be incredibly intimate. Her entire ‘yearning’ for this person is how I felt about that piano melody. The melody was in sync with the lyrics.

'there’s glitter on the floor after the party…’ followed by that piano key that’s unsettling.

I’m sure hardcore fans broke the lyrics down to death by now, but it clearly shows an established relationship, to do things together such as picking up bottles after the party. You know, couple things.

And I think this song isn’t exactly a song for the fans, it’s a song Taylor wrote for herself. A reminder, to hold on, to her, to not read the last page, to not forget her laugh, that everything would be ok. All the things that she wants with her, and while it could have been how much she wants to kiss her, she simply wants to just pick up bottles with her on New Years Day symbolizing a stable relationship for once in her life.

It’s beautiful, it’s sweet, it’s heartwrenching and I really like the song.
